Sample 5:  Demonstrates item deletion without conflict

 

 

Starting State:  v5.xml

 

 

Endpoint 1 updates:

  • Delete item with id=“ep1.101”

 

Endpoint1 output file: ep1_v5a.xml

 

 

Endpoint 2 updates:

  • Delete item with id=“ep2.101”

 

Endpoint2 output file: ep2_v5a.xml

 

 

Merged Result: v6.xml

 

 

Notable Observations:

  • Note that deleted item’s “tombstone” is retained (including item change history)
  • The deleted attribute is set to true for the item’s sx:sync element
  • The item is updated - an item deletion is considered an update operation

 

<item>

<sx:sync id="ep1.101" updates="2" deleted="true" noconflicts="false">

<sx:history sequence="2" when="2007-01-19T00:14:40Z" by="EP1" />

<sx:history sequence="1" when="2007-01-19T00:14:37Z" by="EP1" />

</sx:sync>

<title>Get car serviced</title>

<description>Needs oil change</description>

</item>

 

<item>

<sx:sync id="ep2.101" updates="2" deleted="true" noconflicts="false">

<sx:history sequence="2" when="2007-01-19T00:14:40Z" by="EP2" />

<sx:history sequence="1" when="2007-01-19T00:14:37Z" by="EP2" />

</sx:sync>

<title>Get birthday gift for mother</title>

<description>She likes blue flowers</description>

</item>
